    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1911-05-26T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1911-05-26T00:00:00-05:00" n="731"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d731">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/1879.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Mexican Ambassador</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1911-05-26">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 26, 1911</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 34.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Excellency</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the
                    receipt of your note of the 20th instant in which, by direction of your
                    Government, you communicated to the Department a report that 12 Mexican Federal
                    employees were driven from Tia Juana in the recent attack on that place, fled
                    into the United States, and are detained by the local authorities of San Diego,
                    Cal., where, it is alleged, three of them have been subjected to molestation,
                    presumably by sympathizers with filibusters.</p>
                <p>Agreeably to your request that these Mexican employees be set free, and that
                    their molesters be punished if the report of their wrongful acts shall be
                    verified, I have communicated your note to the Secretary of War and the Attorney
                    General for investigation and appropriate action.</p>
                <p>Accept [etc.],</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">P. C. Knox.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
